            "practice": [
                "Greet someone: Say 'Bihyishum' and introduce yourself with 'Ining <your name>.'",
                "Ask 'Kamm nimf?' and respond with 'Zasiba,' 'Chashum,' or 'Sika.'",
                "Part with 'Dikamaja' to express a friendly departure."
            ],
            "tip": "Visualize a color (e.g., bright red and dark blue for zasiba) while speaking to connect with Shum’s meditative roots."
